{{Infobox FIBA tourney | title = 2015 MVP Cup | subtitle = 2nd MVP Cup | year = 2015 | logo = 2015_mvp_cup_logo.jpg | size = 250 | host = {{PHI}} | dates = September 11–13 | teams = [[#Participants|4]] | federations = 3 | venues = [[#Venue|1]] | cities = 1 | champions = Philippines | title_number = 2 | mvp = | ppg_p = | ppg_t = | rpg_p = | rpg_t = | apg_p = | apg_t = | website = | prevseason = [[2010 MVP Invitational Champions' Cup|2010]] | nextseason = }}
The '''2015 Manny V. Pangilinan Cup''', also known as the '''Master Game Face MVP Cup 2015''' due to sponsorship reasons, was an invitational basketball tournament which was participated by four teams from September 11–13, 2015 at the [[Smart Araneta Coliseum]].<ref>{{ cite news |last1=Bracher |first1=Jane |title=Gilas Pilipinas to play in MVP Cup before FIBA Asia |url=http://www.rappler.com/sports/by-sport/basketball/gilas-pilipinas/98645-gilas-pilipinas-mvp-cup-fiba-asia |work=[[Rappler]]|date=7 July 2015 |accessdate=10 July 2015 }}</ref> While a similarly named tournament was held in 2010, the [[2010 MVP Invitational Champions' Cup]], the 2015 MVP Cup is considered the inaugural edition of the [[MVP Cup]] and is planned to be held annually.<ref>{{ cite news |last1=Joble |first1=Rey |title=Inaugural MVP Cup set for Gilas Pilipinas as tuneup for FIBA Asia |url=http://www.interaksyon.com/interaktv/inaugural-mvp-cup-set-for-gilas-pilipinas-as-tuneup-for-fiba-asia |publisher=InterAksyon.com |date=8 July 2015 |accessdate=10 July 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150710081400/http://www.interaksyon.com/interaktv/inaugural-mvp-cup-set-for-gilas-pilipinas-as-tuneup-for-fiba-asia |archive-date=2015-07-10 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
The tournament was a single-round robin format and the champions were awarded $25,000.<ref>{{ cite news |last1=Giongco |first1=Mark |title=PH to host four-nation MVP Cup as final tune-up before Fiba Asia |url=http://sports.inquirer.net/186296/ph-to-host-four-nation-mvp-cup-as-final-tune-up-before-fiba-asia |publisher=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer#Inquirer.net|Inquirer.net]] |date=7 July 2015 |accessdate=10 July 2015 }}</ref>
==Venue== <center> {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center" !colspan=2|[[Quezon City]] |- | '''[[Smart Araneta Coliseum]]''' |rowspan=3|{{location map+ |Philippines |float=center|width=200 |places= {{location map~ |Philippines |marksize=10 |mark=Red pog.svg |lat=14.620556|long=121.053333|label=Araneta|position=left}} }} |- | Capacity: '''25,000''' |- | [[File:MetroManilajf7543 09.JPG|200px]] |} </center>
==Participants== *{{bk|PHI}} (hosts) *{{bk|TPE}} *{{flagicon|New Zealand}} [[Wellington Saints]] *{{flagicon|PHI}} [[Talk 'N Text Tropang Texters|Talk 'N Text]]
[[China men's national basketball team|China]], [[South Korea national basketball team|South Korea]] and [[Senegal national basketball team|Senegal]] were invited to join the tournament but neither three had confirmed their participation.<ref>{{ cite news |last1=Dy |first1=Richard |title=Gilas-Senegal rematch looms in MVP Cup |url=http://www.philstar.com/sports/2015/07/12/1476148/gilas-senegal-rematch-looms-mvp-cup |date=12 July 2015 |publisher=[[The Philippine Star]] |accessdate=13 July 2015 }}</ref> [[Lebanon national basketball team|Lebanon]] confirmed their participation but later withdrew from the tournament due to undisclosed reasons.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dy|first1=Richard|title=Lebanon pulls out from MVP Cup|url=http://www.philstar.com/sports/2015/09/02/1495179/lebanon-pulls-out-mvp-cup|accessdate=2 September 2015|publisher=The Philippine Star|date=2 September 2015}}</ref> [[Talk 'N Text Tropang Texters]] was a last minute replacement team following the withdrawal of Lebanon.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Leongson|first1=Randolph|title=Tropang Texters join MVP Cup|url=http://pba.inquirer.net/60420/tropang-texters-join-mvp-cup|accessdate=7 September 2015|publisher=Philippine Basketball Association, Philippine Daily Inquirer|date=7 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| last1=Dy| first1=Adrian |title=LOOK 2015 MVP Cup schedule |url=http://www.slamonlineph.com/look-2015-mvp-cup-schedule|accessdate=8 September 2015|publisher=Slam Philippines|date=8 September 2015}}</ref>
