'''Aleksandr Igorevich Bondar''' ({{lang-ru|Александр Игоревич Бондарь}}; born 25 October 1993) is a Russian diver.

==Career==
He competed for Ukraine at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in the [[Diving at the 2012 Summer Olympics – Men's synchronized 10 metre platform|men's synchronized 10 metre platform]].

Bondar moved to Russia at the end of 2014 to be closer to relatives and his Russian girlfriend, Yekaterina Fedorchenko. He and Fedorchenko married in January 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fina.org/athletes/oleksandr-bondar |title=Oleksandr Bondar |website=[[FINA]] |accessdate=3 September 2016}}</ref> In October 2015, he became a Russian citizen.<ref>[http://sport.segodnya.ua/others/ukrainskiy-prygun-v-vodu-bondar-poluchil-rossiyskoe-grazhdanstvo-662423.html Украинский прыгун в воду Бондарь получил российское гражданство]</ref><ref>[http://sport.segodnya.ua/others/trener-sbornoy-ukrainy-o-sbezhavshem-v-rossiyu-sportsmene-eto-predatelstvo-662634.html Тренер сборной Украины о сбежавшем в Россию спортсмене: "Это предательство!"]</ref>

