{{use dmy dates|date=July 2016}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = ECU | NOCname = [[Ecuadorian National Olympic Committee]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1992 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.coe.org.ec }}&nbsp;{{es icon}} | location = [[Barcelona]] | competitors = 13 (6 men and 7 women) | sports = 6 | flagbearer = [[María Cangá]] | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Ecuador]]''' competed at the '''[[1992 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]. Thirteen competitors, six men and seven women, took part in fifteen events in six sports.<ref name="SportsRef">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/ECU/summer/1992/ |title=Ecuador at the 1992 Summer Games |accessdate=23 July 2016 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref>
==Athletics== {{main|Athletics at the 1992 Summer Olympics}}
'''Men's 10.000 metres''' *[[Edy Punina]] ** Heat &mdash; 30:19.76 (→ did not advance)
'''Men's Marathon''' * [[Rolando Vera (athlete)|Rolando Vera]] &mdash; 2:21.30 (→ 43rd place)
'''Men's 20&nbsp;km Walk''' *[[Jefferson Pérez]] &mdash; did not finish (→ no ranking)
'''Women's 3.000 metres''' *[[Janeth Caizalitín]] ** Heat &mdash; 9:32.29 (→ did not advance)
'''Women's 10.000 metres''' *[[Martha Tenorio]] ** Heat &mdash; 34:29.03 (→ did not advance)
'''Women's 10&nbsp;km Walk''' *[[Miriam Ramón]] ** Final &mdash; 51:56 (→ 36th place)
'''Women's 400m Hurdles''' *[[Liliana Chalá]] ** Heat &mdash; 58.55 (→ did not advance)
==Cycling== {{main|Cycling at the 1992 Summer Olympics}} Two male cyclists represented Ecuador in 1992.
;[[Cycling at the 1992 Summer Olympics – Men's individual road race|Men's road race]] * [[Juan Carlos Rosero]]
;[[Cycling at the 1992 Summer Olympics – Men's 1 km time trial|Men's 1 km time trial]] * [[Nelson Mario Pons]]
==Judo== {{main|Judo at the 1992 Summer Olympics}}
* [[María Cangá]]
==Shooting== {{main|Shooting at the 1992 Summer Olympics}}
* [[Hugo Romero]]
==Swimming== {{main|Swimming at the 1992 Summer Olympics}}
'''Women's 100m Breaststroke''' * [[Priscilla Madero]] ** Heat &mdash; 1:20.76 (→ did not advance, 40th place)
'''Women's 200m Breaststroke''' * [[Priscilla Madero]] ** Heat &mdash; 2:46.79 (→ did not advance, 35th place)
==Tennis== {{main|Tennis at the 1992 Summer Olympics}}
'''Women's Singles Competition''' * [[María Patricia Cabrera]]
