{{Refimprove|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Estadio Hernán Ramírez Villegas | nickname = | image = Q 079.JPG | location = [[Pereira, Colombia|Pereira]], [[Colombia]] | broke_ground = | opened = 1 May 1971 | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = Grass | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[Deportivo Pereira]] | seating_capacity = 30,297<ref>Estadio Hernán Ramírez Villegashttp://es.fifa.com/mm/document/footballdevelopment/technicalsupport/01/52/19/97/fu20wcreportv2.pdf</ref> }}
'''Estadio Hernán Ramírez Villegas''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Pereira, Colombia|Pereira]], [[Colombia]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches. It is also the home of [[Deportivo Pereira]]. The stadium holds 30,313 people.<ref name=worldstadiums>Ver [http://www.worldstadiums.com/south_america/countries/colombia.shtml ficha de capacidad según Worldstadiums]</ref> The stadium was built in 1971. The stadium was under reconstruction for the [[FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in 2011.
