{{other people|James Browne}}
'''James Browne''' (born September 15, 1966) is a retired [[long jump]]er, who finished in 17th position at the [[1988 Summer Olympics]] in [[Seoul, South Korea]], as a representative of [[Antigua and Barbuda at the 1988 Summer Olympics|Antigua and Barbuda]].

He attended [[Abilene Christian University]] in Texas where he was a member of the [[Abilene Christian Wildcats]].<ref>http://www.lonestarconference.org/sports/2010/7/28/gen_0728101555.aspx</ref>

