{{BLP sources|date=July 2012}} [[File:Kenita Larraín.jpg|thumb|right|180px|'''María Eugenia Larraín''']] '''María Eugenia Larraín Calderón''' (born October 16, 1973, in [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]]), known as '''Kenita''' (or '''Quenita''') '''Larraín''', is a [[Chile]]an [[Model (person)|model]] and [[socialite]].
Larraín is the daughter of Patricia Calderón Terán and Mario Larraín Corssen, granddaughter of Mario Larraín del Campo and Javiera Corssen Rivera and great-granddaughter Ricardo Larraín Bravo, descendant of the 1st Marquess of Larraín.<ref>[http://www.lanacion.cl/p4_lanacion/antialone.html?page=http://www.lanacion.cl/p4_lanacion/site/artic/20040131/pags/20040131185807.html ] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604040130/http://www.lanacion.cl/p4_lanacion/antialone.html?page=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lanacion.cl%2Fp4_lanacion%2Fsite%2Fartic%2F20040131%2Fpags%2F20040131185807.html |date=June 4, 2011 }}</ref> Larraín is of [[Basque people|Basque]] descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lanacion.cl/p4_lanacion/antialone.html?page= |accessdate=December 1, 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110622063327/http://www.lanacion.cl/p4_lanacion/antialone.html?page= |archivedate=June 22, 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lanacion.cl/p4_lanacion/site/artic/20040131/pags/20040131185807.html |title=nacion.cl - El golazo de Kenita |publisher=Lanacion.cl |date=2004-01-31 |accessdate=2012-07-21}}</ref><ref>[http://www.exonline.com.mx/diario/noticia/funcion/musica/kenita_larrain_en_busca_del_sol/793389 ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100220051325/http://www.exonline.com.mx/diario/noticia/funcion/musica/kenita_larrain_en_busca_del_sol/793389 |date=February 20, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.genealog.cl/Chile/L/Lecaros/ |title=Familia Lecaros - www.genealog.cl |publisher=Genealog.cl |date=2004-08-23 |accessdate=2012-07-21}}</ref>
She studied at Liceo Manuel de Salas in [[Ñuñoa]], [[Santiago Province, Chile|Santiago]]. She studied engineering at UNIACC University, a second-tier private college, graduating in 2003.
In 2008 Larraín participated in the Argentine television show [[Bailando por un sueño (Argentina)|Bailando por un Sueño]] and in 2009 joined the Chilean reality show [[Pelotón VIP]] with her twin brother Mario Larraín. She was first runner-up. In 2011 she starred in the [[music video]] of Evailo ("Moya E"), a [[Bulgaria]]n [[singer]] known in Chile for competing in the TV show ''Yingo''. In November 2011 released her first single "Mi Mundo Sin Ti," a cover version of the song by [[Spain|Spanish]] singer [[Soraya Arnelas]].
