{{infobox country at games|NOC=NOR|NOCname=|games=Deaflympics|year=2017|flagcaption=|oldcode=|website={{url|http://www.doveidrett.no/}}|location=[[Samsun]]|competitors=7|sports=|flagbearer=|rank=|gold=1|silver=0|bronze=1|officials=|appearances=|app_begin_year=|app_end_year=}}
'''[[Norway]]''' competed in the [[2017 Summer Deaflympics]] which was held in [[Samsun]], [[Turkey]]. Norway sent a delegation consisting of 7 participants for the event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deaflympics.com/games.asp?2017/nor|title=Norway {{!}} 2017 Summer Deaflympics|last=|first=|date=|website=www.deaflympics.com|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-12-18}}</ref>This was the 20th consecutive time that Norway went onto participate at the [[Deaflympics|Summer Deaflympics]] since making its Deaflympic debut in 1931.
Norwegian athletes claimed 2 medals in the event including a gold medal and a bronze medal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deaflympics.com/countries.asp?country=NOR&medalists=41|title=Countries {{!}} Deaflympics|website=www.deaflympics.com|language=en|access-date=2017-11-18}}</ref> [[Trude Raad]] won the women's hammer throw event and broke her own world record in the women's hammer throw after claiming gold medal with a record time of 66.05<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://deaflympics2017.org/en/rekorlarin-sehri-samsun-detail/284|title=Deaflympics 2017 Samsun|website=deaflympics2017.org|language=tr|access-date=2017-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deaflympics.com/games.asp?results/deaflympics/2/3217|title=Women's hammer throw {{!}} 2017 Summer Deaflympics|last=|first=|date=|website=www.deaflympics.com|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-12-18}}</ref>
