{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Olympia Park Stadium | image = | location = [[Rustenburg, North West|Rustenburg]], [[South Africa]] | coordinates = {{coord|25|39|45|S|27|13|19|E|display=it}} | broke_ground = | opened = 1989 | renovated = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Rustenburg, North West|City of Rustenburg]] | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = | seating_capacity = 32,000 }}
'''Olympia Park''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] located in [[Rustenburg, North West|Rustenburg]], [[South Africa]]. Not to be confused with the [[Royal Bafokeng Stadium]], where the [[2010 FIFA World Cup]] games were played, it is currently used mostly for [[Association football|football]] and [[Rugby union|rugby]] matches; it was utilized as a training field for teams participating in the 2010 FIFA World Cup.<ref>http://www.sa2010.gov.za/en/highlights-2010</ref>
== Notable matches ==
=== 1995 Rugby World Cup === During the [[1995 Rugby World Cup]], the stadium hosted three group-stage matches.<ref>http://2010worldcupsouthafrica.com/2010-world-cup-cities/rustenburg-city-profile.php</ref>
{{clear}} {| class="wikitable" style="text-align: left;" width="100%" |- !Date !Team #1 !Res. !Team #2 !Round !Attendance |- |1995-05-26||{{ru|Côte d'Ivoire}} ||style="text-align:center;"|0–89||{{ru|Scotland}}||[[1995 Rugby World Cup|Group D]]||style="text-align:center;"|20,000 |- |1995-05-31||{{ru|France}} ||style="text-align:center;"|54–18||{{ru|Côte d'Ivoire}}||[[1995 Rugby World Cup|Group D]]||style="text-align:center;"|17,000 |- |1995-06-04||{{ru|Côte d'Ivoire}} ||style="text-align:center;"|11–29||{{ru|Tonga}}||[[1995 Rugby World Cup|Group D]]||style="text-align:center;"|16,000 |}
The stadium irregularly hosts [[Premier Soccer League|ABSA Premiership]] games.
