{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = W. H. Laverton's Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Westbury, Wiltshire|Westbury]], [[Wiltshire]] | establishment = 1888 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1890 | club1 = W. H. Laverton's XI | date = 11 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/829.html Ground profile }}
'''W. H. Laverton's Ground''' was a [[cricket]] ground in [[Westbury, Wiltshire|Westbury]], [[Wiltshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1888, when W. H. Laverton's XI played O. G. Radcliffe's XI.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/829_misc.html Other matches played on W. H. Laverton's Ground]</ref> The ground hosted a single [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match in 1890, which saw W. H. Laverton's XI playing the touring [[Australia national cricket team|Australians]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/829_f.html First-Class matches played on W. H. Laverton's Ground]</ref> The final recorded match held on the ground saw Leighton play [[Lansdown Cricket Club|Lansdown]] in 1899.
The ground's exact location is unknown, but its approximate location would be somewhere within the grounds of Leighton House, which is today home to the [[Army Officer Selection Board]].
